    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 13,
        "summary": "The way of the transgressor is hard\u2014Evil pursues sinners\u2014He who does not discipline his children hates them.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "A wise son heareth his father's instruction: but a scorner heareth not rebuke.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A man shall eat good by the fruit of his mouth: but the soul of the transgressors shall eat violence.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that keepeth his mouth keepeth his life: but he that openeth wide his lips shall have destruction.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Silence.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 77
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The soul of the sluggard desireth, and hath nothing: but the soul of the diligent shall be made fat.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apathy; Laziness.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A righteous man hateth lying: but a wicked man is loathsome, and cometh to shame.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Righteousness keepeth him that is upright in the way: but wickedness overthroweth the sinner.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 11:5 (3\u20136); D&C 133:44.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "There is that maketh himself rich, yet hath nothing: there is that maketh himself poor, yet hath great riches.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 11:24; Matt. 16:26.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 6:7.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 109
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The ransom of a man's life are his riches: but the poor heareth not rebuke.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The light of the righteous rejoiceth: but the lamp of the wicked shall be put out.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 18:5; Prov. 24:20.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Only by pride cometh contention: but with the well advised is wisdom.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:25.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Wealth gotten by vanity shall be diminished: but he that gathereth by labour shall increase.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 13:19.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vanity.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Industry; Labor.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Hope deferred maketh the heart sick: but when the desire cometh, it is a tree of life.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso despiseth the word shall be destroyed: but he that feareth the commandment shall be rewarded.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:16; Morm. 9:26.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 98
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The law of the wise is a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 10:11; Moro. 7:11.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Good understanding giveth favour: but the way of transgressors is hard.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Every prudent man dealeth with knowledge: but a fool layeth open his folly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A wicked messenger falleth into mischief: but a faithful ambassador is health.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Poverty and shame shall be to him that refuseth instruction: but he that regardeth reproof shall be honoured.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 15:5.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 95:1; 121:43.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The desire accomplished is sweet to the soul: but it is abomination to fools to depart from evil.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that walketh with wise men shall be wise: but a companion of fools shall be destroyed.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Evil pursueth sinners: but to the righteous good shall be repayed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 32:10.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A good man leaveth an inheritance to his children's children: and the wealth of the sinner is laid up for the just.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 2:26.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Much food is in the tillage of the poor: but there is that is destroyed for want of judgment.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that spareth his rod hateth his son: but he that loveth him chasteneth him betimes.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 29:15.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 4:14; D&C 68:28. TG\u00a0Chastening; Family, Children, Responsibilities toward.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The righteous eateth to the satisfying of his soul: but the belly of the wicked shall want.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 34:10; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:51 (50\u201351).",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 38
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}